<section xml:id="PYTHAGOREAN-THEOREM" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>PYTHAGOREAN THEOREM</title>

  <p>
    For all right angle triangles, you can use the Pythagorean Theorem (C2 = A2 + B2) or  [SOH | CAH | TOA] to solve for unknown angles or lengths.
  </p>


  <blockquote>
    <p>
       <term>PYTHAGOREAN THEOREM</term> (<m>C^2 = A^2 + B^2</m>)
    </p>
    <p>
      <m>\sin \theta = \frac{\text{Opposite}}{\text{Hypotenuse}}</m> (SOH)
    </p>
    <p>
      <m>\cos \theta = \frac{\text{Adjacent}}{\text{Hypotenuse}}</m> (CAH)
    </p>
    <p>
      <m>\tan \theta = \frac{\text{Opposite}}{\text{Adjacent}}</m> (TOA)
    </p>
  </blockquote>

  <figure xml:id="pythagorean_theorem_1">
    <caption>
      For example, to solve for angle <m>\beta</m>, you can use the following equations: <m>\sin \beta = \frac{A}{C}</m>, <m>\cos \beta = \frac{B}{C}</m>, or <m>\tan \beta = \frac{A}{B}</m>.
    </caption>
    <image source="images/pythagorean_theorem_1.png" width="40%"></image>
  </figure>

</section>